Conclusion:

Breastfeeding (nursing or pumping) is an incredible amount of work, especially in the first few months after baby’s born. Without support from spouse or family, it is an impossible feat (I have been very lucky to have an awesome husband who does half or more of everything).


Returning to work, without a supportive culture, breastfeeding cannot be sustained and motherhood is ten times more difficult than it should be.


Kudos to all moms who barely left the house, carried (or have been carrying) a huge sleep debt, followed a restrictive diet, and of course whose breasts have become a war-torn zone. Your baby is one of the luckiest that enjoyed the fruits of your work.


Happy Mother’s Day (from one mom to all others)!
